The picture, taken ahead of Order of the Garter Service at St George's Chapel, saw the 96-year-old monarch pose with Prince Charles and the Duchess of Cornwall. She has been pictured using a walking stick at most events in recent months. But the latest images appear to show a crutch, rather than a standard walking stick. This comes as she has been suffering from "episodic mobility issues", a palace source said. UPDATES TO FOLLOW...